There was carnage and chaos on the N2 south bound near Joyner Road in Umbogintwini, south of Durban, a short while ago, where two men were killed in a horrific crash that caused the vehicles to rip apart. Netcare 911 and other emergency service providers responded to the collision where there were reported entrapments. Media liaison officer for Netcare 911, Shawn Herbst said: “Reports indicate that a bakkie and car were involved in a collision resulting in both vehicles being torn apart. Medics assessed the scene and found that two people, both adult males, had sustained fatal injuries and were sadly declared deceased on the scene by a Netcare 911 emergency care practitioner. Three other people had sustained moderate injuries and were treated on scene before being transported to hospital for further care.”